<br>
I do need to point out, however, something that made it less rewarding for some, and may cause some to be reluctant to raid with Instant Army again.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>NBG - Any 'upgrades' will be given to those people that last the entire raid. Extra armor will be divied out for greed (everyone will roll - highest number will pick first from list of armor available; lowest number will pick last.) - Just like my last couple of fear raids...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Everything that dropped from Cazic Thule would have been an upgrade for most of the people present.  No where in your posting was it mentioned that CT drops were going to be reserved or restricted.  &quot;ANY&quot; upgrades were to be for &quot;those people that last the entire raid.&quot;<br>
<br>
Also, there were many SK and Ranger armor drops that most certainly were greed rolled afterward, but only by Instant Army members.<br>
<br>
Now, this little bit gets you off the hook, as it were...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>l rules subject to change, and I have final say on all decisions.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That's all nice, but it does not change the impression of some that you witheld the rolling restrictions until the very end, in order to keep people in the raid to ensure your success.  <br>
<br>
This left such a bad taste in many people mouths, that I was told by several people that they would not raid with you again.  Perhaps you don't care?  Who needs them anyway?  Of course, one could take that kind of approach.  It does not make good friends, though.<br>
<br>
I will gladly come on any Open Fear raid you host.  I have no problem with &quot;you scratch my back&quot; etc. especially if it is clear beforehand.  I have a Guild with over 100 Bards, and nothing but Bards.  We all need an Amygdalyn Tendril for our Epics, and we cannot do it by ourselves.<br>
<br>
I also had a lot of fun, btw.  So I will happily go wherever and kill whatever, pretty much any time.  I thought you should know, though, that your last minute announcement made many people very unhappy.<br>
